    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <p>I have just received your card,<ptr target="med.00642_n1"/> dated 28th September, and I am very glad to hear that
                you have had so pleasant a summer, and that you are in better health.<ptr target="n0905"/> Long may you
                remain so, say I. Did you receive a letter I sent you some weeks ago, asking you to
                write four or six lines in an MS. poem by Walter Scott?<ptr target="med.00642_n2"/> Not hearing from you, I fear
                you have not received it. If you have not received it, may I send it to you again,
                when I will explain my wishes? It will only occupy you for five minutes. I spent a
                very pleasant hour yesterday with Lowell. We smoked the pipe of
                good-fellowship. Tennyson is in Sussex, quite well. I shall send him your card.</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>Yours,</salute>
                <signed>F. Locker.</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
